\title{BFHcharts: SPC Visualization for Healthcare Quality Improvement}
\description{
BFHcharts provides modern, publication-ready Statistical Process Control (SPC)
charts for healthcare quality improvement. Built on ggplot2 and qicharts2,
it offers:
\itemize{
\item Beautiful themes with hospital branding support
\item High-level convenience functions for quick plotting
\item Low-level API for advanced customization
\item Comprehensive SPC chart types (run, I, P, U, C, etc.)
}
}
\section{Main Functions}{

The package exports one primary function:
\itemize{
\item \code{bfh_qic()} - High-level wrapper for complete SPC workflow
}

Additional exported utilities:
\itemize{
\item \code{bfh_export_pdf()}, \code{bfh_export_png()} - Export charts to PDF/PNG
\item \code{bfh_extract_spc_stats()}, \code{bfh_merge_metadata()} - Utility functions
}
}

\section{Design Philosophy}{

Inspired by BBC's bbplot, BFHcharts follows these principles:
\itemize{
\item Reproducibility through standardization
\item Beautiful defaults with flexible customization
\item Modern tidyverse-compatible API
\item Comprehensive documentation and examples
}
}

\section{BFHtheme dependency}{

BFHcharts requires \verb{BFHtheme >= 0.5.0} for theming, color palettes and
scale helpers. \code{BFHtheme} is hosted as a GitHub-only package via the
\verb{Remotes:} field; install with \code{pak::pkg_install("johanreventlow/BFHcharts")}
or \code{remotes::install_github("johanreventlow/BFHtheme@v0.5.0")} to ensure
it is present.

If \code{BFHtheme} is missing or older than 0.5.0, BFHcharts emits a
\code{packageStartupMessage()} at \code{library(BFHcharts)} and fails fast with an
actionable install hint at the first plot call. The check is cached per
session for performance.
}

